Process = running program with its own memory.

PID = Process ID (unique number).

fork() → creates a child process (duplicate of parent).

	Returns 0 in child process.

	Returns child PID in parent process.
	

exec() family → replaces current process image with a new program (ls, date, etc.).

wait() / waitpid() → parent waits until child finishes.


👉 Interview Question: “What’s the difference between fork() and exec()?”

	fork() → creates new process.

	exec() → runs a new program inside the process.
